def: A massive and fibrous mineral of a whitish color, chieflyhydrous silicate of lime.
Broiled or fried after being split lengthwise; -- said of eels.
A white person; -- an appellation supposed to have been appliedto the whites by the American Indians. J. F. Cooper.
A process of bone formation in which ossification takes placein the perichondrium and either surrounds or gradually replaces thecartilage.

A genus of small beetles, several of which, in the larvalstate, are very destructive to woolen goods, fur, etc. The common"museum pest" is A. varius; the carpet beetle is A. scrophulariæ. Thelarvæ are commonly confounded with moths.
Quality or state of being weasy; full feeding; sensualindulgence. [Obs.] Joye.
Any one of many species of long-legged dipterous insectsbelonging to Tipula and allied genera. They have long and slenderbodies. See Crane fly, under Crane.
